.SH NAME
dotty-security-key-remove - Remove security key aliases.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdotty security-key remove [--name=] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Remove one alias by --name, or pick aliases interactively: a tree grouped
by serial number — collapsible with h/l, filterable with / — where space
selects and enter confirms. A key may carry several aliases, so multiple
selections are removed in one go.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for remove

.PP
\fB--name\fP=""
	alias to remove


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile to operate on (defaults to the active profile)

.PP
\fB--serial\fP=""
	serial number of the security key


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  dotty security-key remove --name=old-key
  dotty security-key remove
  dotty sk --serial=12345678 rm
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdotty-security-key(1)\fP
